					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-609114#post-1845578</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-609114/scp-1517#post-1845578</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Sep 2013 14:52:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NovaSeaker</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>358117</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>+1 for the moment I read that the eggs were composed of saccharides, realized that not only do the eggs LOOK like candy, but TASTE like it too, and that when you suck on one long enough and/or bite into it HUNDREDS OF INSECTS BURST INTO YOUR MOUTH AND START EATING YOUAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH</p> <p>Wasn't much of a fan of the candy-golem at the end though. It felt a bit tacked on, because it wasn't given an SCP-1517-B designation, and wasn't also contained, but rather incinerated. A candy golem seems pretty anomalous to me, and worthy of being part of the whole SCP. But, wasn't enough to keep me from upvoting.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
